The paper deals with sampling from lattice Gaussian distribution, which is a problem in information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SI). The paper also discusses Markov chain Monte Carlo (MCMC) methods, which is a topic in machine learning and statistics (cs.LG). The paper also involves convergence analysis and enhancement of the sampling algorithm, which can be categorized under numerical analysis (cs.NA) and data structures (cs.DS).
